post_text: Wonderful Go Green Ribbon Project for the Kearney Recycling Center to plant a tree from the Gibbon FBLA! Thanks to Delaney Tracey and her Go Green Committee for completing this project.
shared_text:
City of Kearney Nebraska Government
April 22 at 10:23 AM ·

Happy Earth Day!

How are you celebrating? Our Sanitation Department celebrated by planting a Bald Cypress tree at our Recycling Center. Thanks to a generous donation from Gibbon High School FBLA, they helped purchase this tree as a part of their Go Green Ribbon Project. The Bald Cypress Tree will grow up to 55 feet tall and have a spread of 30 feet. What a beautiful addition to the Kearney Area Recycling Center.

According to an article in today's Omaha World Herald, 75 million people are now working from home. With the addition of kids being e-schooled the burden on WI-FI home routers is increasing daily. Here are a few tips that may increase the speed of the network within your home. If you are needing more speed, please give us a call at (308) 468-6341. We are EXTENDING our free month, no contract, no setup fee offer through the end of April on all new accounts and speed upgrades.

post_text:
TRACK CLOTHING APPAREL ORDER
All

NSAA has postponed the start of track season at least until May 1st. I have NOT ordered the 2020 track apparel yet. If we have 50 items I will still place the orders for those that want their shirts and refund the money/return checks to those that no longer wish to order the items. If we reorder I will

REMOVE THE YEAR so they'll be "good" for years to come.

Please let me know YES or NO by Wednesday, April 1st.

EMAIL ME: leon.stall@gibbonpublic.org or TEXT ME: be sure to include your name.

Thank you.

Coach Stall

All NSAA activity practices and competitions are suspended through May 1st. These suspensions may be extended should the conditions warrant.

Member schools and student-participants are expected to adhere to the NSAA Constitution & Bylaws and activity manuals during this time.

The NSAA encourages all member schools to follow CDC, local, state and federal health department recommendations.

As more information becomes available, official updates will be posted on the NSAA website and the NSAA social media platforms.

If you have any questions please contact Mrs. Waddle. Thank you.

shared_text:
UNK.EDU
Coder Dojo | Cyber Systems | University of Nebraska at Kearney

Ross Taylor
February 12 at 3:04 PM ·

This Monday, February 17th, the University of Nebraska at Kearney Department of Cyber Systems is hosting a Coder Dojo event from 6 - 8 p.m on the UNK campus in Otto Olsen room 110. If you have a child who would like to participate please follow the link for free registration.

CoderDojos are on the 3rd Monday of the month in February, March, and April for the Spring semester.

CoderDojos are unstructured, open-source coding clubs. Ages 8 to 17 will be introduced to computer programming. Parents are welcome.

There is no cost to attend. Students may attend as few or many events as they would like.
